>self</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Handler.html#Std.Http.Server.Handler\">Handler</a> <span class=\"fn\">σ</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">σ</span> → <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">request</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Http/Data/Request.html#Std.Http.Request.Head\">Request.Head</a>) → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Async/Basic.html#Std.Async.Async\">Async.Async</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Called when a request includes an `Expect: 100-continue` header. Return `true` to send a\n`100 Continue` response and accept the body. If `false` is returned the server sends\n`417 Expectation Failed`, disables keep-alive, and closes the request body reader.\nThis function is guarded by `Config.lingeringTimeout` and may be cancelled on server shutdown.\nThe default implementation always returns `true`.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Server/Handler.html#Std.Http.Server.Handler.onContinue","kind":"def","line":57,"name":"Std.Http.Server.Handler.onContinue","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Http/Server/Handler.lean#L57-L57"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Handler.html#Std.Http.Server.Handler.onFailure\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Handler</span>.<span class=\"name\">onFailure</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">σ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Htt